					<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><h3> <span class="mw-headline" id="Seven_Sources_of_Waste_.28Muda.29">Seven Sources of Waste (Muda)</span></h3>
<ol>
<li>Overproduction. - Mismatch between supply and demand. To produce sooner or in greater quantities than         customers requires.</li>
<li>Transportation. - Unnecessary movement of parts or people between processes.</li>
<li>Rework. - Repeating or correcting an operation because of quality problems. “Do it right at the first time”</li>
<li>Over-processing. - Processing beyond what the customer requires.</li>
<li>Motion. - Unnecessary movement of parts or people within a process. </li>
<li>Inventory. - The worst source of waste. Number of flow units in the system.  For physical products: raw  material, work in progress or finished products.</li>
<li>Waiting. - Underutilizing people e or parts while a process completes a work cycle,</li>
</ol>

